-- Bank of Spain Governor to Explain Role in Bankia, Mundo Says
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-05-13T15:13:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-13/bank-of-spain-governor-to-explain-role-in-bankia-mundo-says.html
The Bank of Spain Governor Miguel Angel Fernandez Ordonez will be asked to explain in the Spanish
Congress the regulator’s role in the supervision of Bankia
Group, El Mundo said.  The parliamentarian group of the ruling People’s Party
plans to file a request for the governor’s appearance in the
coming days, the newspaper said citing lawmaker Vicente Martinez-Pujalte. Bankia Group was nationalized May 9.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Ross-Thomas in Madrid at 
 erossthomas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  